parameters:
[Servant] If you wish to recall your magic, please speak to Lady Rade.
If you bring a gift that pleases Lady Rade, you will be able to
remember. However, you cannot recall high-level magic if Luna's level
is too low.

[Servant] As for gifts for Lady Rade, it doesn't have to be cake or
sweets; any present that seems to delight Lady Rade will do. Please
find something wonderful during your adventure.

※During your adventure, you will find "Gifts for Rade" in treasure
chests and various places. Acquire these gifts and give them to Rade
to help her remember her magic.
\C[27][Rade]\C[0] No way! Absolutely not, not, not, not! Nooo!

\C[24][Becky]\C[0] Sigh... Luna, it's useless to ask Rade. Let's think of another
way.

\C[24][Cain]\C[0] Another way? Even with Regnus Grahardt, we can't beat the guys
from Valentia, and we can't defeat Lucia, right?

\C[23][Luna]\C[0] Rade-sama, is it true that even with Regnus Grahardt we can't
beat the generals of Valentia or Lucia? I at least want to confirm
that.
\C[27][Rade]\C[0] There's no way Regnus would bother with you guys~.
\C[24][Becky]\C[0] But...! The Magic General Rinny said so.

[Servant] If I may speak... if that person is truly Lord Regnus
Grahardt, I believe he wouldn't lose to the generals of the magic
kingdom Valentia or someone named Lucia.

[Servant] Yes, if that person is truly Lord Regnus Grahardt... that
is.
\C[23][Luna]\C[0] Even the servant is certain... You must be very confident.

\C[24][Becky]\C[0] Hey servant, who exactly is Regnus Grahardt? And who are you
guys? It's about time you told us, don't you think?

[Servant] Lord Regnus Grahardt and Lady Rade are, to put it cheaply,
what you'd call rivals.

[Servant] If I say Lord Regnus is an individual with power equal to
Lady Rade, that should convey the idea to you all.
\C[27][Rade]\C[0] You're a servant, you should be praising your master~.
[Servant] Speaking the truth is also part of a servant's role.
\C[27][Rade]\C[0] It's frustrating~. It makes me angry~.

\C[24][Becky]\C[0] Wait a minute. Rade, if you and Regnus have equal power, then
you could just take Regnus Grahardt's place, right?
\C[24][Becky]\C[0] It would be as if Regnus Grahardt were here.
\C[27][Rade]\C[0] What~? Why do I have to take Regnus's place~?

\C[24][Cain]\C[0] Can't be helped. If Rade won't help us, then we really have no
choice but to look for Regnus Grahardt.

\C[24][Cain]\C[0] Just to confirm, if it's really Regnus, he can beat the generals
of Valentia and Lucia, right?

[Servant]: Lord Regnus Grahardt is somewhat more reasonable than Lady
Rade. If you can find him, he might be willing to lend you his
strength.
\C[23][Luna]\C[0] Is that so... Just hearing that gives me some relief.
\C[27][Rade]\C[0] Hey, servant~ You don't need to say anything unnecessary~.

[Servant]: It's strange, though. There have been many sightings of
Lord Regnus in this country of Jupiterino.

[Servant]: However, whether that person is the real Lord Regnus
Grahardt we are looking for, I cannot say.

\C[24][Becky]\C[0] Wait a minute, Rade. For a sorceress of your caliber to be in
the vast world of the Jupiterino continent, and just to search for
Regnus Grahardt...

\C[24][Becky]\C[0] Why did you choose Jupiterino? You know a lot about Regnus
Grahardt, don't you?

[Servant]: Sharp... Indeed, I too was curious about the reason for
coming to Jupiterino.

\C[24][Becky]\C[0] Rade, what do you have to say? Why did you think Regnus
Grahardt would be in Jupiterino?
\C[27][Rade]\C[0] Ugh~ I'm not obligated to tell you guys about Regnus's past~!

[Servant]: Lord Regnus's past? This is the first time I've heard of it
as well.
\C[24][Becky]\C[0] Hey, Rade, what kind of past does Regnus have?
\C[27][Rade]\C[0] Enough! If you pry any further, I'll get angry~!

\C[24][Becky]\C[0] Good grief. But it seems we're back to square one with our
original goal.

\C[23][Luna]\C[0] Yes. It seems we have no choice but to search for Regnus
Grahardt. We can't beat them with our power alone. Right, servant?

\C[23][Luna]\C[0] Servant, do you know of any places where Regnus Grahardt might
have stopped by? I think it's faster to ask you than to rely on
information from others regarding this matter.
\C[27][Rade]\C[0] No way. We're not involved~. And I won't lend you the servant~.

\C[24][Becky]\C[0] Ugh...! Rade, you came to Jupiterino to search for Regnus
Grahardt too, didn't you?

\C[24][Becky]\C[0] You might not like cooperating with us, but we're offering to
search in your stead, right? Our goals are the same, aren't they?

\C[24][Becky]\C[0] It's settled then. Servant, tell us the places where Regnus
Grahardt might have stopped by. We've got Rade's permission now.

[Servant]: Understood. Perhaps there is some fate between us. I don't
have any leads, but I can investigate the traces where Lord Regnus
Grahardt has walked.
\C[24][Becky]\C[0] As expected of a servant! More capable than the master, huh-.
\C[27][Rade]\C[0] Hey~ Don't do things on your own~.

[Servant]: What's the harm? We too are tired of searching for Lord
Regnus. Let me investigate and inform you.

[Servant]: Hmm... this is surprising indeed. There are certainly
traces of Lord Regnus Grahardt having walked in various places. It's
unclear what his purpose for coming to Jupiterino is, though.

\C[24][Cain]\C[0] If you could do that, you should have started investigating like
that from the beginning.

[Servant]: Well... using such magic doesn't feel good, you know. It's
creepy for both the searcher and the searched.

\C[24][Becky]\C[0] From my point of view, it's creepy not knowing who you guys
really are.
[Servant]: Ah... haha... that is a secret.

[Servant]: The places where Lord Regnus Grahardt has walked are often
dangerous. It might be too much for you to handle. Are you still going
to go? There's no guarantee that Lord Regnus will become your ally,
you know?

\C[23][Luna]\C[0] Yes, we'll go! Right now, all we can do is follow the shadow of
Regnus Grahardt. When we find him, we'll definitely make him our ally
and return.
[Servant]: Is that so? Then please speak to me once you are ready.
